  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use Heyting algebras when you can:\nStart from a lattice with top ⊤\\top and bottom ⊥\\bot. Define an implication operation a⇒ba \\Rightarrow b for every pair of elements. Accept that some elements may lack complements — excluded middle may fail. ¶Definitions A bounded lattice is a lattice with a greatest element ⊤\\top and a least element ⊥\\bot.\nA Heyting algebra [@esakia_HeytingAlgebras_2019] is a bounded lattice (H,≤,∧,∨,⊥,⊤)(H, \\leq, \\wedge, \\vee, \\bot, \\top) equipped with a binary operation ⇒\\Rightarrow (called Heyting implication) satisfying:\n",
